cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.SD

This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques to improve the performance of a game-playing agent. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves language grounding, which is a subfield of NLP, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another likely category. The use of neural networks and learning strategies also suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible category. The paper also involves game theory and decision-making, which could fall under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the use of Monte Carlo Search framework suggests cs.SD (Systems and Control) as a possible category.
